race.comment: MOUNT SABYINYO (6) bumped into a good one on debut at Cranbourne and went right on with it next time out, scoring by 3.5 lengths. The overall time was just fair but he did it easily there on speed and looks progressive. He maps nicely here off the low gate and can go on with it. OFF THEIR PERCH (11) has placed in both runs back and should be ready to peak now. She'll be the one sitting off speed and finishing strongly late. ORNOS (2) resumes. He took on some good races last time in, with form around Group performed horses. This looks a good race for him if he's returned well - watch the market. ECO FORCE (13) has been close up in two runs back, good out to 1200m at Cranbourne second up. She sets up ideally from the gate and will be hard to hold out.
